Em nenhum momento queremos prejudicar estudantes de escola pÃºblica. Estamos lutando pelos direitos de estudante de baixa renda que foram bolsistas integrais ou parciais em escolas privadas, estudantes com deficiÃªncia que estudaram em escola privada e estÃ£o sendo excluÃ­dos do Prouni. Se houve a criaÃ§Ã£o de uma categoria para estudantes de escola particular e nenhum estudante dessa categoria estÃ¡ sendo contemplado, criou-se outra distorÃ§Ã£o, outra exclusÃ£o. Por isso, Ã© justo que haja uma reserva pra alunos bolsistas integrais e parciais, visto que esses alunos tambÃ©m se enquadram nos critÃ©rios de baixa renda e cursaram escolas privadas apenas por intermÃ©dio de bolsas, nÃ£o possuindo recursos para pagar integralmente cursos como medicina, por exemplo.
comment: We need your help to end the injustice in the Prouni program. Our demand is solely for reserved places for scholarship recipients from private schools. At no point do we want to harm public school students. We are fighting for the rights of low-income students who were full or partial scholarship recipients in private schools, and students with disabilities who studied in private schools and are being excluded from Prouni. We do not want competition between public school students and students from private schools. If a category was created for private school students and no student from this category is being considered, another distortion, another exclusion, has been created. Therefore, it is fair that there be a quota for full and partial scholarship recipients, since these students also meet the low-income criteria and attended private schools only through scholarships, not having the resources to fully pay for courses such as medicine, for example.

comment_pt: PerdÃ£o, deputados, mas hÃ¡ um erro na proposta. O foro que se pretende acabar deixou de ser privilegiado, por decisÃ£o do STF. Passou a ser um foro comum, um juÃ­zo criminal "competente" para julgar qualquer um dos 200 milhÃµes de brasileiros. As demais instÃ¢ncias foram relegadas ao papel de simples auxiliares do juÃ­zo Ãºnico e universal, onde 11 "brilhantes" "juizes" tem a primeira, a Ãºltima e a Ãºnica palavra, jÃ¡ que nem mesmo a defesa Ã© autorizada a se pronunciar (e quando o faz, Ã© solenemente ignorada, com a cumplicidade da OAB). EntÃ£o, a medida correta seria o impechman do presidente do Senado, Rodrigo Pacheco, por omissÃ£o voluntÃ¡ria e descumprimento do dever funcional, seguido do processo de impedimento de cada um dos atuais ministros - com amplo direito de defesa, em respeito Ã  ConstituiÃ§Ã£o- permanecendo no cargo apenas aqueles que forem absolvidos pelo tribunal competente. Os demais, passarÃ£o a responder criminalmente por seus atos, a partir da primeira instÃ¢ncia, com o devido processo legal, como manda a Carta PolÃ­tica. @carla.zambelli @sostenescavalcante
comment: Excuse me, members of parliament, but there is an error in the proposal. The jurisdiction that is intended to be abolished is no longer privileged, by decision of the Supreme Federal Court. It has become a common jurisdiction, a criminal court "competent" to judge any of the 200 million Brazilians. The other instances have been relegated to the role of mere auxiliaries to the single and universal court, where 11 "brilliant" "judges" have the first, the last, and the only word, since not even the defense is allowed to speak (and when it does, it is solemnly ignored, with the complicity of the Brazilian Bar Association). Therefore, the correct measure would be the impeachment of the Senate president, Rodrigo Pacheco, for willful omission and breach of duty, followed by the impeachment process of each of the current ministers â€“ with full right of defense, in respect of the Constitution â€“ with only those acquitted by the competent court remaining in office. The others will be held criminally responsible for their actions, starting from the first instance, with due process of law, as mandated by the Constitution. @carla.zambelli @sostenescavalcante
